casebody.data:
The People, etc., ex rel. Rudolph Grancher, Relator, Appellant v. Charles F. MacLean, et al., Commissioners, etc., Respondents. *465Decided July 5, 1892. Appeal by writ of certiorari by relator from judgment of the board of police commissioners imposing upon relator a fine of five days’ pay. Louis J. Grant, for relator, appellant. William H. Clark, counsel to the corporation, for respondents.

Before Freedman, P. J., Dugro and Gildersleeve, JJ.

Per Curiam.

Judgement of commissioners and writ dismissed, with $50 costs and disbursements.
